# POLIS — Simulation Model

All line numbers refer to `index.html` and are approximate.

## Core data

- **Grid**: `G` = grid size (selectable 32/64/128 via `WORLD_SIZES`).
  `map[y][x]` is a **cell**: `{ t:type, lv:level 0–7, dev:growth progress,
  pw:powered, wt:watered, fire, vary:render noise, grp:[rootX,rootY],
  part:bool, bld:construction%, bridge, bus, rail, rz:rubble-origin type }`.
  Helpers: `idx(x,y)=y*G+x`, `inB(x,y)` bounds check.
- **Scalar fields** (Float32Array, length G*G), recomputed in
  `recomputeFields()` (~1985): `pollution`, `leisure`, `crime`, `landVal`,
  and `cover.{police,fire,school,health,transit}`. `splat()` paints a radial
  falloff. Land value blends pollution, traffic, service coverage, leisure,
  nearby water/trees, and crime.
- **Global state `S`** (~1011): `money, tax, day, speed, diff, pop, jobs,
  happy, demand{r,c,i}, zoom/ox/oy (camera), tool, overlay, rot, milestone,
  fund{police,fire,school,health}, policy{}, loan, power/water caps`.

## The tick loop

`loop()` (~13540) runs on `requestAnimationFrame`. A fixed-step accumulator
calls `simTick()` per game day; speed → step from `TICK_MS=[∞,560,280,130]`.
**Rendering is decoupled** from the sim and throttled by a frame governor
(`PERF.saver`); the simulation always runs at full fidelity regardless of FPS.

`simTick()` (~3064) each day: fire spread + rubble cleanup → per-cell zone
**growth/decay**, then aggregates education & crime, recomputes demand,
demographics & happiness, and every 30 days runs the **monthly budget** +
autosave. Per-level-up field recomputes are coalesced via `RF_DEFER` into one
`recomputeFields()` pass per tick.

## Growth model (the heart of the game)

A zoned lot (`res`/`com`/`ind`) levels up only when gated by:
**adjacent road** (`roadAdj`), **power** (`pw`), **water** (`wt`), positive
**demand**, **land value** thresholds, and for high tiers **education**
(`S.edu`) and **leisure**. Levels 1→7; mature lv3 lots `tryMerge()` (~2800)
four neighbors into a 2×2 **tower** (`grp`/`part`), which can rise to
skyscraper / highrise / megatower. Unpowered/unwanted lots decay and
downgrade; `unmerge()` breaks towers back down (or to `rubble` after fire).

`CAP` (~2745) = population/jobs per type per level; the level-up gates and
promotion odds live in the **`GROWTH`** table beside it. `D = S.demand` is
recomputed from the jobs↔pop↔commerce↔industry balance minus a tax drag
(coefficients in **`DEMAND`**); happiness weights live in **`MOOD`** and the
`S.happyParts` breakdown sums to the mood target by construction. A
**demographics layer** (child/work/senior cohorts eased by health, education
and happiness) sets `S.labor`, which feeds back into demand.

## Economy

`computeBudget()` (~2907), applied monthly in `simTick`:
- **Income** = (`resTax = pop*tax*0.26` + `jobTax = jobs*tax*0.36`) × difficulty
  `d.inc` + **tourism** (working airports, capped) + **trade** (see below),
  all × `kmRamp()`.
- **Costs** = road/avenue/path/busstop/rail upkeep (scaled by congestion wear
  and an infrastructure-**ageing** multiplier `ageMul`, diluted by fresh
  build-out) + service `svcCost` (`UPKEEP` × funding sliders `S.fund` ×
  population load × difficulty) + emissions levy + ordinances (`polBudget`).
- `S.net = income − roadCost − svcCost − emitCost − adminCost − polCost − loanPay`;
  added to `S.money`. `adminCost` (`max(0,pop−ADMIN_FREE)×ADMIN_RATE×d.up`) is
  the per-capita civic overhead that cancels the otherwise-unbounded late-game
  income runaway.
- **Trade/GDP** (~2884–2960): industry produces goods, pop+commerce consume
  them; surplus exports via border/seaport/airport freight capacity (income
  capped by `TRADE_INCOME_CAP`), deficits import at bulk/spot prices. A
  derived GDP headline anchors tax income.
- **Ordinances** `POLICIES` (~1384): 8 toggleable policies with monthly
  cost/income (`polBudget` ~1422) and field effects (pollution, crime,
  education, demand, mood).
- **Difficulty** `DIFF` (~1358) scales growth/income/upkeep/disaster rates;
  the top level uses the escalating `kmRamp()` (~1367) no-win ramp.
  **Loans**: `LOAN_OFFERS` (~12798), `takeLoan`/`repayLoan`, one at a time,
  amortized monthly.

## Networks (power, water, traffic)

Roads carry **cars, power, and water**. `recomputePower()` (~1761) and
`recomputeWater()` (~1849) flood-fill conductivity (`CONDUCT`) from plants
(`PLANT`) / sources (`WSRC`) across roads + buildings; call both via
`recomputeNets()`. **Traffic is routed, not splatted**: `recomputeCommute()`
(~3429) runs multi-source Dijkstras over the road graph with BPR-style
congestion-priced edges (`buildStepCost` ~3380), and `emitCommute()` (~3463)
walks each lot's work/shop/leisure trips down the cost gradient onto the
`traffic` Float32Array (decayed daily). `congestion()` = traffic / `ROAD_CAP`
(~1722); gridlock chokes growth and land value, and unreachable jobs feed a
happiness penalty. Sanitation is its own network: garbage collected over the
road net into landfills/recycling/incinerators, landfills fill up.

## Agents & rendering

- Agents: `cars[]` (`stepCars` ~3556), `peds[]` (~3676), `planes[]` (~7702),
  `trains[]` (~7712), ships, service vehicles (`svc` — fire engines really
  extinguish; the rest are cosmetic).
- **Isometric renderer**: `isoX/isoY/toScreen` (~4291), tile `TW=64,TH=32`,
  4 rotations (`rotate`, `rotC/rotD`), painter's-algorithm in `render()` (~9350).
  Per-type draw fns: `drawZone`, `drawRes/drawCom/drawInd`, `drawBigBuilding`,
  `drawVenue`, `drawTowerTile`, `civic`, `drawAirport`. Buildings are procedural
  geometry (`box`/`vol`/`cyl`/`windows`/`gable`). Day/night (`duskAmt`),
  weather (`WX`, `drawPrecip`), and seasons (`SEAS`/`updateSeason`) modulate it.
- **Render caches** (don't bypass them): a baked ground plane (`PERF.gnd`),
  LRU sprite caches for zoned single lots (`VARN`/`blitLot`; `SPR_LIVE` lists
  the variants that must stay live) and 2×2 towers, and a whole-world snapshot
  (`bakeWorld`) used at far zoom / mid-gesture on heavy maps.

## Other systems

Disasters (`triggerDisaster` ~15132/`stepDisaster`), scenarios (`SCEN` ~14534,
`startScenario`), milestones/ranks (`MILESTONES` ~1287), undo/redo
(`undoStack`), generative WebAudio music + SFX (`audioInit`, `musicLoop`,
multiple styles), PWA install (`pwaInit`, procedurally-drawn app icon) with an
offline shell in `sw.js`, and accessibility wiring (dialog roles + focus
management, one central block near the end of the script).
